    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p><strong>Usage</strong> drawn on a creature or object</p><hr /><p>This vertical rune is often carved on tall towers to draw lightning and shield the buildings below it. If the bearer does not take a move action at least once on its turn, lightning finds it at the end of its turn, dealing @Damage[(1d4 + (ceil(@actor.level/2)) - 1)[electricity]].</p><p><strong>Invocation</strong> The preliminary streaks of lightning braid together into a powerful bolt. The rune-bearer takes @Damage[(2*ceil(@actor.level / 2))d6[electricity]] damage, with a @Check[fortitude|basic|against:runesmith] save.</p><hr /><p><strong>Level (+2)</strong> The damage increases by 1, and the damage of the invocation increases by 2d6.</p>"
